leisure /ˈlɛʒə/

1. N-UNCOUNT Leisure is the time when you are not working and you can relax and do things that you enjoy. 空闲时间 

例： ...a relaxing way to fill my leisure time. …我消磨空闲时间的一种放松方式。 

2. PHRASE If someone does something at leisure or at their leisure , they enjoy themselves by doing it when they want to, without hurrying. 悠闲地 

例： You will be able to stroll at leisure through the gardens. 你将能在花园里悠闲地散步。

